6: O-oh no! My spear, why isn't it—AAH!
20:
Well, at least the sand broke your
fall. Wasn't that spear supposed to
help you fly?
24:
Something feels off. It's as though
the winds here are... stagnant.
27:
The air is so heavy. It pulls me down
when I try to fly, as though it were
holding me hostage...
33:
Sounds as if the very nature of this
world is reflected in the air itself.
That's likely what you're feeling.
38:
A brutal world, ruled by a brutal
regime... Even the sky itself seems on
the verge of being swallowed by the
sands.
41:
Exactly. The very oppressiveness of
this world might be what's affecting
your ability to fly.
46: ...That will not stop me from trying!
50:
W-wait a second! You shouldn't go
alone!
61:
Thank you for treating my injuries! 
I would have been in trouble
otherwise...
64:
I'm just glad you aren't hurt. But lady,
if you don't mind me asking... How
did you just fly—
66:
Boy! What do you think I'm payin'
you for? Get back to work or you can
find somewhere else to stay!
69:
That man... I take it he isn't your
father.
72:
...I work here. My village... It was
pillaged by raiders, so...
75:
Raiders? So that means, your
family... They're...
78:
...I'm one of the lucky ones, really. 
At least I'm here. Alive.
89:
No, thank you. Seeing you fly like
that was something else. It's been a
while since I felt so thrilled.
92:
I... I will be flying around here
tomorrow as well!
96:
So... I could take you for a ride? 
Only if you are interested, of course!
108:
I hope that boy enjoys his time in
the sky with you, Zephyr.
112:
I hope so too. It may be imprudent
of me to say this... but I am quite
excited!
116:
Beats sittin' around looking all
gloomy, that's for sure. 
C'mon, let's go.
122:
You're right! I will be sure to
welcome him with a warm smile—
125:
...There is a smell of smoke in the
wind. It's coming from... Oh no. The
boy's village?
134:
Raiders! They must've attacked
during the night...
138:
Nothing else to do but follow their
trail. No guarantee they'll be alive,
but... it's worth a try.
146:
I swore to fly with him! What makes
me any different from that boy?
Why... Why must he...
151:
That's just what life's like in these
parts. Nothing any of us can do
about it.
155:
I know. I know that I am simply one
of the lucky ones.
157: But... still! The boy, he should...
162:
You seemed quite earnest in your
attempts to reach out to him.
165:
With determination like that, I know
you'll find a means of helping the
boy yet.
170: ...I shall do what I can! Onwards!
187:
We have come to rescue you.
Come, let us leave here!
192:
This is my fate now. I should just...
give up—
195: But fate is what brought us together!
198:
And if fate decides to cast you
down...
202:
...Then my wings, and my spear,
shall lift you up once more!
206:
Looks like I made it just in time.
How's about we teach these
bastards a lesson?
211: I believe that sounds in order!
218:
Heehee... See? Flying is easier than
you think.
221:
...I wish I could fly like you, lady. 
I know it's impossible, but...
224: You should not give up so easily!
226:
You may not have wings, but there
are plenty of ways to fly. You could
ride an "aero-plane," or—what are
those large balloons called? "Plimps"?
230:
...If I'm able to fly someday, you're
gonna be the first person I take with
me!
233: I shall keep you to your word!
